Source: screentime-guardian
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Florian <florian@example.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.0
Homepage: https://github.com/petrockblog/screentime-guardian

Package: screentime-guardian
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, systemd, dbus, avahi-daemon, libnotify-bin
Description: Screen time management daemon for Linux Mint
 A parental control application that enforces per-user screen time limits
 on Linux systems. Features include:
  - Per-user daily time limits
  - Web-based mobile-friendly control interface
  - On-screen countdown warnings
  - Time extension capability
  - Session locking via systemd-logind
  - mDNS discovery (screentime-guardian.local)
